AIG Denies Moor Full Target Bonus After $4.2 Billion Shortfall

-- B y   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 
2011-03-17T22:17:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/aig-denies-moor-full-target-bonus-after-4-2-billion-shortfall.html
  American International Group Inc. (AIG) ’s
Kristian Moor, head of the bailed-out insurer’s property-
casualty division, was denied his full target bonus after the
business he oversees reported a $4.2 billion reserve shortfall.  Moor was awarded incentive pay of $1.71 million, or 90
percent of the $1.9 million target set for him, the New York-
based insurer said in a regulatory filing today. His salary is
$5 million in stock and $700,000 in cash, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Frye in New York at 
